## How Conditional Statements Work
<img src="https://images.code.org/cfb8d737716d4fac85a487abe934f6be-image-1741630391959.png" alt="code with conditional statement" width="350px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 0 40px 40px;">

#### Use **methods** to check a condition
#### The method will return a **boolean**, true or false
- #### If **true**, the code inside the conditional block **runs**
- #### If **false**, the code inside the conditional block is **skipped** 

<div style="clear:both;"></div>

---

## Simplifying with Functions

<img src="https://images.code.org/6b626f9a3a0340f417f6813e5713c512-image-1743444908994.png" alt="code with conditional statement" width="350px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 0 40px 40px;">

#### In the previous prediction level, this conditional was put into a function to simplify the code. 

#### This way, the programmer can simply call the function using the function name instead of making if statements over and over. 

